text: Claudia Cagninelli (born 19 July 1990 in Trescore Balneario) is an Italian volleyball player. She played at the 2007 FIVB Girls' Youth World Championship, and 2008 Women's Junior European Volleyball Championship, winning a gold medal. At the club level, she played for Volley Bergamo and ICOS Crema. == References == Category:Italian volleyball players Category:1990 births Category:Living people
